Afro-fusion Daniel Benson known professionally as Bnxn and formerly known as Buju has highlighted how social media has impacted artistes. The “Finesse” singer, in a viral video, was seen in the company of Grammy-winning singer, Wizkid and Afro-rave artiste, Rema having fun in a club after they gave thrilling performances at a show in Malta. Reacting to their time at the club, BNXN noted social media continues to fuel competition among artistes who would ordinarily rather compliment and complement one another if it was solely left to them.   We’ll fix Justices’ complaints on work…     Remaining kidnapped railway passengers must be rescued…     Portable needs rehabilitation, says Okowa’s aide   According to BNXN: “Last night was sexy af, I realised that social media has created some sort of barrier between artistes who actually have the same goal and mentality towards things. “Like we just wanna take care of our family and have money in our pocket. “Like, we gave each other our flowers to our faces because social media would make it weird cause everything is fuelled by competition.”